---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy and Cookie Policy">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-6">
    <h1
      class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold mb-12 text-center tracking-tight text-accent-text"
    >
      Privacy & Cookie Policy
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-12 text-text/80 leading-relaxed font-light">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading mb-4 text-text">
          Data Controller
        </h2>
        <p>
          <strong>MEGASHOP ARREDI</strong><br />
          Via Nazionale, 4 - 92010 Alessandria della Rocca (AG) - Italy<br />
          VAT: 02913370843<br />
          Contact Email: <a
            href="mailto:info@megashoparredi.it"
            class="text-accent-text hover:underline">info@megashoparredi.it</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading mb-4 text-text">
          Types of Data Collected
        </h2>
        <p>
          Personal Data collected by this Website, independently or through
          third parties, include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-4 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Navigation data:</strong> information about devices,
            browsers, and network connections used to visit the site.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Data entered in the contact form:</strong> name, email, phone
            number, and any other information voluntarily provided by the user
            to request assistance or additional information.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Interaction with external widgets:</strong> use of services
            such as Google Maps which may collect anonymous data on network traffic
            and preferences for statistical or display purposes.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading mb-4 text-text">
          Purpose and Legal Basis for Processing
        </h2>
        <p>
          User Data is collected to allow the Controller to provide
          its Services, as well as for the following purposes: contacting
          the User, providing quotes and assistance, and displaying content
          integrated from external platforms.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The legal basis for processing is, depending on the case, the user's
          explicit consent (for example, for sending messages via
          forms), the execution of a pre-contractual or contractual request, or
          the legitimate interest of the Controller in the correct and safe
          functioning of the website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading mb-4 text-text">
          Processing Methods and Retention Times
        </h2>
        <p>
          The Controller adopts appropriate strict security measures aimed at
          preventing unauthorized access, disclosure, modification, or destruction
          of Personal Data.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Data is processed at the Controller's operating offices and in any
          other place where the parties involved in the processing are
          located.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Data is kept for the time strictly necessary to
          achieve the purposes for which it was collected, or until
          the User's consent is revoked for treatments based on
          this foundation, without prejudice to any obligations provided for by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading mb-4 text-text">
          Rights of the Data Subject
        </h2>
        <p>
          Users can exercise certain rights at any time
          under the European GDPR Regulation (Art. 15 et seq.), in particular
          the rights to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-4 space-y-2">
          <li>
            Access their own Data knowing the purposes and methods of
            processing;
          </li>
          <li>
            Verify its correctness and request its integration or
            updating;
          </li>
          <li>
            Obtain the cancellation and permanent removal of their own Personal
            Data;
          </li>
          <li>
            Object to the processing itself or request a temporary
            limitation;
          </li>
          <li>
            Freely withdraw previously given consent
            whenever desired.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          To exercise their rights, the User can direct a
          request to the contact details of the Controller freely indicated
          in this document. Such requests are processed free of charge as
          soon as possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading mb-4 text-text">
          Cookie Policy
        </h2>
        <p>
          This site uses "Cookies", which are small fragments of text
          sent by your browser and saved on your device, to make
          the user experience simpler and more efficient.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-heading text-text mb-2">
              Essential Technical Cookies
            </h3>
            <p>
              They are necessary for the correct functioning of the site and to
              allow correct navigation between pages. Being
              strictly necessary and not performing user profiling,
              they do not require explicit consent from
              the User.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-heading text-text mb-2">
              Third-Party Cookies
            </h3>
            <p>
              The site may include third-party components and plugins
              (such as, by way of example, the embedding of
              Google Maps) which may use profiling and tracking cookies in various ways.
              These cookies are managed
              entirely by the relevant providers and are subject to their
              respective privacy or cookie policies. The User is
              invited to read the extended regulations provided by the relevant
              third parties to know how to deny consent.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
